# Casai — environment template
# Copy to `.env` and fill in. `.env` is gitignored; this file is not.
#
# Both values below are PUBLIC. The anon key is designed to ship in the
# client bundle — it identifies the project, it does not authorise anything.
# Data is protected by Row Level Security (supabase/migrations/0002), which
# is why the boundary was built before the client was wired.
#
# NEVER put the service_role key, the database password, or a personal
# access token in this file or any other file in the repo. The service_role
# key bypasses RLS completely and would undo the entire authorization model.

# Project Settings → API → Project URL
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co

# Project Settings → API → anon / public key (also shown as "publishable")
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key

# Region note: the project must be created in South Asia (Mumbai, ap-south-1).
# Aadhaar-linked and personal data stays in India under the DPDP Act, and a
# project's region cannot be changed after creation.
